            ğŸ² Play board games<br>
            ğŸ‘¥ Chat about daily life activities<br>
            Connect, grow, and have fun with us! ğŸŒŸ
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Feature 4 -->
      <div class="flex items-start text-left p-4 bg-[#1B262C] rounded-lg shadow-md">
        <Icon name="job-interview" class="w-6 h-6 sm:w-8 sm:h-8 mr-3 sm:mr-4 text-gray-300" />
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold mb-2">Job Interview</h3>
          <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gray-300">
            <span class="text-[#fb6526]">60%-70%</span> of job candidates fail due to poor soft skills.<br>
            <span class="text-[#fb6526]">57%</span> are rejected for lack of soft skills (LinkedIn Survey).<br>
            Soft skills impact <span class="text-[#fb6526]">75%</span> of hiring decisions (Harvard Business Review).
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Feature 5 -->
      <div class="flex items-start text-left p-4 bg-[#1B262C] rounded-lg shadow-md">
        <Icon name="cv-cover-letter" class="w-6 h-6 sm:w-8 sm:h-8 mr-3 sm:mr-4 text-gray-300" />
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold mb-2">CV and Cover Letter</h3>
          <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gray-300">
            <span class="text-[#fb6526]">40%-60%</span> of applicants are declined due to poor CVs and cover letters.<br>
            <span class="text-[#fb6526]">45%</span> of recruiters reject candidates for this reason (Jobvite).<br>
            <span class="text-[#fb6526]">58%</span> of hiring managers cite this as a key factor (CareerBuilder).
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Feature 6 -->
      <div class="flex items-start text-left p-4 bg-[#1B262C] rounded-lg shadow-md">
        <Icon name="ielts" class="w-6 h-6 sm:w-8 sm:h-8 mr-3 sm:mr-4 text-gray-300" />
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold mb-2">IELTS</h3>
          <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gray-300">
            <span class="text-[#fb6526]">25%</span> report increased salary from improved language skills.<br>
            <span class="text-[#fb6526]">50%</span> see career growth with strong IELTS scores.<br>
            <span class="text-[#fb6526]">60%</span> of immigration authorities use IELTS for visas.<br>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
